<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="PubMed-not-MEDLINE" Owner="NLM"><PMID Version="1">35193263</PMID><DateRevised><Year>2022</Year><Month>02</Month><Day>23</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">2470-0053</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>105</Volume><Issue>1</Issue><PubDate><Year>2022</Year><Month>Jan</Month></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Physical review. E</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Phys Rev E</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Nonergodicity of reset geometric Brownian motion.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>L012106</StartPage><MedlinePgn>L012106</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1103/PhysRevE.105.L012106</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>We derive. the ensemble- and time-averaged mean-squared displacements (MSD, TAMSD) for Poisson-reset geometric Brownian motion (GBM), in agreement with simulations. We find MSD and TAMSD saturation for frequent resetting, quantify the spread of TAMSDs via the ergodicity-breaking parameter and compute distributions of prices. General MSD-TAMSD nonequivalence proves reset GBM nonergodic.</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Vinod</LastName><ForeName>Deepak</ForeName><Initials>D</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Institute of Physics and Astronomy, University of Potsdam, 14476 Potsdam-Golm, Germany.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Cherstvy</LastName><ForeName>Andrey G</ForeName><Initials>AG</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Institute of Physics and Astronomy, University of Potsdam, 14476 Potsdam-Golm, Germany.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Institut f&#xfc;r Physik, Humboldt-Universit&#xe4;t zu Berlin, 12489 Berlin, Germany.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Wang</LastName><ForeName>Wei</ForeName><Initials>W</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Max Planck Institute 